HEADWORD: Durbar
<hw>Dur"bar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>darb⟦amac⟧r</ets>, fr. Per <ets>dar<?/⟦amac⟧r</ets> house, court,
hall of audience; <ets>dar</ets> door, gate + <ets>b⟦amac⟧r</ets> court,
assembly.]</ety> <def>An audience hall; the court of a native prince; a
state levee; a formal reception of native princes, given by the governor
